). An investigation of the rotational splitting of the\noscillation frequencies of the star yields no conclusive evidence on the\nstellar inclination angle. We further obtained Rossiter-McLaughlin\nobservations, which result in a broad posterior of the stellar obliquity. The\nplanet seems to conform to the same patterns that have been observed for other\nsub-Saturns regarding planet mass and multiplicity, orbital eccentricity, and\nstellar metallicity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 May 2018 17:05:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-13"}
